     FFUUNNCCTTIIOONN
          HHeellpp prints documentation (if it exists) for each named
          topic.  Complete  on-line  documentation is resident on
          the Micronix system.
          
          HHeellpp is the same program as mmaann,, execpt that when it is
          called as "help" it looks first in /usr/help for a file
          with the same name as the given topic. Then, like  mmaann,,
          it searches /usr/man/man0, ..., /usr/man/man9 in order.
          These  are the directories containing the corresponding
          sections of the Micronix Reference Manual:
          
                /usr/man/man1   Programs
                /usr/man/man2   System Entries
                /usr/man/man3   Libraries and subroutines
                /usr/man/man4   Devices
                /usr/man/man5   File formats
                /usr/man/man6   Other programs (such as CP/M programs)
          
          
          The  "N"  option  directs  hheellpp  to  the  corresponding
          section of the manual.
          
          
